name: Entering a Show
description: The information on the entry form is entered into a database which is used to generate the show catalog. Each cat entered in the show is listed in the catalog. An entry will look like this in the show catalog: The line with “AA BB CC DD EE FF” indicates the initials of the judge in each ring. The next line is the BREED, which is followed by the CLASS NUMBER, COLOR and SEX. The NAME of the cat is shown on the same line as the ENTRY NUMBER and a space to mark awards received in each ring.
